  section
    h2 Creating the item texture
    ul
      li Open Paint.Net
      li Create a 16x16 Image
      li save it as a .png
  
  section
    h2 Adding the item to the game
    ul
      li Open up your exampleMod from yesterday in eclispe
      li Create a new package: <code>NAME.firstitem</code>
      li Create a new class with your item name and place the follow code:
        pre
          code(data-trim contenteditable)
            | package gmackie.firstitem;
            | import net.minecraft.creativetab.CreativeTabs;
            | import net.minecraft.item.Item;
            | public class MyFirstItem extends Item
            | {
            |   public MyFirstItem()
            |   {
            |     // This is the constructor for our new item. 
            |     // Set basic properties in it.
            |     setMaxStackSize(64);
            |     setCreativeTab(exampleTab);
            |     setUnlocalizedName("MyItem");
            |   }
            | }
  // MIGHT HAVE TO ADD STUFF HERE ABOUT IMPORTING STUFF!

  section
    h2 Adding the item to the game
    ul
      li Go to the exampleMod.java file from yesterday
      li Add the following code inside the <code>preInit()</code> function
        pre
          code(data-trim)
            | MyFirstItem first = new MyFirstItem();
            | GameRegistry.registerItem(first, "MyItem"); 
            | // This name doesn't have to be same as unlocalised name, 
            | //but no harm in them being the same
      li Press <code>ctrl+shift+O</code> to import all the right stuff above
  
  section
    h1 Run the game!
    h3 You should see your item with the default texture in the example tab

  section
    h2 Creating the Language file
    ul
      li Create a new package in the <code>/src/main/resources</code> folder
      li I called mine <code>assets.gmackie.lang</code> (you can change the middle)
      li Add a new file called <code>en_US.lang</code>
      li Place the following into the new file:
        pre
          code(data-trim)
            | item.MyFirstItem.name=Graham's Special Coin

  section
    h2 Adding in the texture
    ul
      li Create a new package in the <code>/src/main/resources</code> folder
      li I called mine <code>assets.gmackie.textures.items</code> (you can change the middle)
      li Place your newly created <code>.png</code> file inside the package
      li Add a new file called <code>en_US.lang</code>
      li Place the following into the <code>preInit()</code> function:
        pre
          code(data-trim)
            | first.setTextureName("gmackie:coin");
      li <code>gmackie</code> is whatever you've been putting in the package names
      li <code>coin</code> is whatever you named the <code>.png</code> file

  section
    h1 Run it again!
    h3 This time your item should have a proper name and texture!

