  section
    h2 Adding the block to the game
    ul
      li Create a new class with your block name and place the follow code:
        pre
          code(data-trim contenteditable)
            | package gmackie.firstitem;
            | 
            | import net.minecraft.block.Block;
            | import net.minecraft.block.material.Material;
            | import net.minecraft.creativetab.CreativeTabs;
            |  
            | public class MyBlock extends Block
            | {
            |   public MyBlock()
            |   {
            |     // This is the constructor for our new item. Set basic
            |     // properties in it.
            |     super(Material.iron); // Copy the properties of iron
            |        
            |     setCreativeTab(CreativeTabs.tabBlock);
            |     setBlockName("MyBlock"); 
            |     // This is the internal name, not display name
            |   }
            | }
  // MIGHT HAVE TO ADD STUFF HERE ABOUT IMPORTING STUFF!

  section
    h2 Adding the item to the game
    ul
      li Go to the exampleMod.java file from yesterday
      li Add the following code inside the <code>preInit()</code> function
        pre
          code(data-trim)
            | // Register my block and set its texture
            | MyBlock b = new MyBlock();
            | 
            | // requires .png file with this name
            | b.setBlockTextureName("gmackie:mblock"); 
            | GameRegistry.registerBlock(b, "MyBlock");
            |
      li Press <code>ctrl+shift+O</code> to import all the right stuff above
  
  section
    h1 Run the game!
    h3 You should see your item with the default texture in the example tab

